name: Seconds
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in seconds.

name: Minutes
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in minutes.

name: Hourly
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in hours.

name: Daily
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in days.

name: Weekly
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in weeks.

name: Monthly
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in months.

name: Quarterly
about: Managing, guiding, and restricting plan entries in quarters.

name: Annually

name: Access
about: Where access to an API is on the table, and might not be publicly available, or part of all plans.

name: Endpoints
about: Providing access constraints based specifically on API endpoints allowing granular controls over each available resource.

name: Overview
about: Provide a single landing page, available at a simple URL, with all the information about plans available as part of platform operations.

name: Overview
about: Providing an overview of what geographic regions are covered or available as part of API consumption.

name: Overview
about: A single page which provides an overview of limits that are in place on API operations.

name: Add-Ons
about: Factoring the availability of add-ons into specific API plans or overall API operations.

name: Verbs
about: Allowing access controls applied down to the HTTP verb level, providing granular controls for GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and other dimensions of resources.

name: Private
about: Is this plan a private one, available only to a limited audience.

name: Calls
about: The most fundamental metric for APIs, the API call.

name: Country
about: Providing API access or replication within specific countries.

name: Inline
about: Providing information about rate limits inline, either within documentation or available within API response details.

name: Connectors
about: Factoring the availability of 3rd party or internal platform connections into specific API plans or overall API operations.

name: Range
about: Considering a range of values when measuring API consumption, and evaluating plan level access.

name: Public
about: Is this a publicly available API operation, something that may only apply to some plans.

name: Value
about: What is the value of an API or endpoint, is it simple 1, or maybe 10, allowing for multiple value settings.

name: Region
about: Providing API access or replication within specific regions.

name: Free
about: Is this a free resource, or set of resources, something that may not apply to all plans.

name: Transaction
about: Allow for the concept of transactions to exist which may span multiple API calls, moving a single concept forward.

name: On-Premise
about: Providing API deployment locally or within existing infrastructure, providing on-premise access levels.

name: Resources
about: Limits are place upon specific endpoints or verbs, providing granular controls over API resources.

name: Trial
about: Is there a trial period that is limited by number of days, which may not apply to all plans.

name: Count
about: Tracking by the count of something, could be API calls, files, or any other county of objects that are part of API operations.

name: Co-Location
about: Allowing for access of API resources via colocated facilities.

name: Increased
about: Opportunities for increasing rate limits either by changing plans, or simply requesting limits to be raised.

name: Demo
about: This resource or set of resources has a demo associated with it, which might apply to multiple plans.

name: Instances
about: Allowing for instances of resources that are available via an API platform, and can be used in different ways within existing plans.

name: Unlimited
about: The ability to overcome limits, and achieve unlimited access to resources.

name: Access
about: Access should not be taken for granted, requiring you to request access, or elevated access levels.

name: Matches
about: Allowing for the measurement of API access in terms of when pre-defined matches are returned, rather than all of the results.

name: Service Level Agreement (SLA)
about: A service level agreement (SLA) is applied as part of API operations as a whole, or as part of particular plans.

name: Setup
about: What are the costs associated with setting up and configuring an account for API access.ttt

name: Message
about: Charging per message rather than each API call that is required to prepare, send, or access messages.

name: API
about: There is an API specifically for accessing limitations around API resources for API consumers to use.

name: Volume
about: Volume is used as a basic measurement of how consumers can access API, providing a standard set of pricing, as well as volume pricing.

name: On-Demand
about: The resource or set of resources can be deployed, and shut down on demand.

name: Reserved
about: There are opportunities to reserve an instance of a resource or set of resources for specific time frames.

name: Compute
about: Providing API resource access based upon various levels of compute power.

name: Volume
about: Volume pricing levels are available, with plans based entirely on volume level access to resources.

name: Load Balancing
about: Measurement of resource usage, based upon the amount of load balancing that occurs.

name: Spot
about: There is an opportunity to big on resources in a localized or distributed marketplace driven environment.

name: Dedicated
about: Resources can be allocated in a dedicated state, remaining available with no downtime, or according to SLA.

name: Storage
about: Measuring API resources based upon the size on the disk.

name: Infrequent
about: Resources are accessed infrequently, treating them as warehoused, or off to the side.

name: Uploads
about: Restricting and measuring API access based upon the number of file uploads.

name: Archive
about: Resources are in an archived state and require very little access, and can be stored in different manner.

name: Upload Size
about: Restricting and measuring API access based upon file upload size.

name: Subscription
about: There is a regular, recurring element to accessing a resource, as part of a larger subscription part of, or separated from plans.

name: Upload Speed
about: Restricting and measuring API access based upon file upload speed.

name: Personal
about: There is a personal element to a set of resources, meant for the casual user, and probably not developing an application or custom integration.

name: Records
about: Measuring API access based upon the number of records accessed or returned.

name: Commercial
about: There is a commercial licensing element to a set of resources, which require additional business or legal requirements.

name: Containers
about: Measuring API access based upon the number of folders, buckets or virtual containers deployed.

name: Non-Commercial
about: The platform allows for non-commercial access to resources, which usually means there is additional commercial requirements.

name: Transcripts
about: Measuring API access based upon the transcripts generated.

name: Educational
about: A platform provides considerations for K-12 or higher educational access to resources.

name: Bandwidth
about: Measuring API access based upon the amount of bandwidth used.

name: Wholesale
about: There are wholesale options around deploying and accessing resources that are available via a platform.

name: Connections
about: Measuring API access based upon the number of connections or threads made to resources.

name: Government
about: A set of API resources is available specifically for government access, meeting the specialized needs of local or federal government use.

name: Simulations
about: Measuring API access based upon the number of simulations generated.

name: Internal
about: A set of resources are tailored specifically for internal consumption rather than for public or partner level acess.

name: Transfers
about: Measuring API access based upon the number of transfers that are executed.

name: Partner
about: There is a focus on partner access to resources, resulting in separate access layers, and features dedicated to partner level consumption.

name: Transfer Limits
about: Using the ability to change transfer limits as a metric in API consumption.

name: Reseller
about: There are reseller opportunities in place around resources available via the platform.

name: Sync
about: Measurement for API consumption based upon the number of syncs that are exected.

name: Venture
about: There are venture opportunities around a platform and the resources available, allow for investments to be made, or possibly received.

name: Conversions
about: Measurement for API consumption based upon the number of conversions that are executed.

name: Type
about: Are there custom types of plans available, with a grouping dimension that goes beyond just the available plans.

name: Syndication
about: Measurement for API consumption based upon how much syndication occurs.

name: Connectors
about: Measuring API access baed upon the number of connectors that are employed, or part of account access.

name: Marketing
about: Is a big part of API operations about driving marketing efforts for other aspects of business operations.

name: Relationships
about: Measuring API access baed upon the number of relationships between users and objects that are established or accessed.

name: Branding
about: Is there a strong brand aspect to API operations, with clear guidelines, resources, and a presence for the companies brand.

name: Migrations
about: Measurement of API accessed based upon the number of migrations that occur.

name: SaaS
about: Is the API operations secondary to a strong SaaS focus for a platform.

name: Archives
about: Measurement of API accessed based upon the number of archives that are created.

name: PaaS
about: Is the API operations secondary to a strong PaaS focus for a platform.

name: Rollback
about: Measurement of API accessed based upon the number of rollbacks that are executed.

name: Traffic
about: Is a primary focus of an API platform centered around driving traffic to a web or mobile presence.

name: Tasks
about: Using the number of tasks that are started or completed as a measurement of API access.

name: Content
about: One of the primary objectives for API resources existing is in support of acquiring data and content that fuels platform operations.

name: Events
about: Measuring of API consumption based upon the number of events that occur or are triggered.

name: Trainings
about: Measurement based upon the number of trainings that occur around API access.

name: Products
about: An API primarily exists to support the existence, or drive the sales of another product, or product line.

name: Maintenance
about: Measuring maintenance events that occur, and affecting API consumption based upon.

name: Services
about: API resources exist to support other related services, and act as value-add to the primary business focus.

name: Latency
about: Measuring the latency that occurs as part of API access, and allowing it to impact API consumption plans.

name: Syndication
about: API resources exist to encourage syndication of data, content, and other digital resources.

name: Performance
about: Using performance as a consideration when measuring API consumption.

name: Analytics
about: A set of API resources exist to gather, refine, and organize data for the purpose of driving analytics.

name: Users
about: Using the number of users as a metric when it comes to planning, and pricing adjustments.

name: Reporting
about: A set of API resources exist to gather, refine, and organize data for the purpose of driving reporting efforts.

name: Media
about: Measuring specifically media related considerations as part of API consumption tracking.

name: Talent
about: API resources are focused on driving talent acquisition, or even placement with ecosystem related companies or as part of wider services.

name: Scan
about: Measure the scanning of a physical or digital object involved in API operations.

name: Security
about: Access to API resources provide a security benefit, or are in support of other related security products and services.

name: Support
about: Directly using support elements as a consideration in API resource planning and consumption.

name: Terms of Service
about: API resources allow for the dynamic configuration of available terms of service that cover access and usage of resources.

name: Fees
about: Fees that are used as part of API accounts, and consumption, and applied as part of API plans.

name: Governance
about: API resources are focused on governance related tasks within a company or possibly a wider industry.

name: Percentages
about: The application of various percentages as part of measuring API consumption, and plan operation.

name: Donations
about: API resources allow for, or depend on donations as part of platform operations.

name: Consulting
about: Factoring in hourly consulting as part of API consumption, and plan operations.

name: Grants
about: API resources exist because of grant related resources, which pay for their design, deployment or operations.

name: Priority
about: Providing the option of being prioritized in API requests and responses, and measured as part of overall planning.

name: Advertising
about: API resources exist in support of advertising related elements of platform operations, driving advertising, or possibly alleviating the need for advertising to be present.

name: Groups
about: API access adjusted based upon grouping, or group level access which is aside from standard plans.

name: API
about: There are APIs available to access all or part of the plans, pricing, or limitations around an API platform operations.

name: Zone
about: Another form of grouping API access, into zones, allowing consumers to access and use resources by zone.

name: Organization
about: There are organizational elements around API access and usage for API consumers to take advantage of.

name: Memory
about: Allowing for the measurement of resource access to be determined by the amount of memory available or consumed.

name: Customization
about: There are customization opportunities around API plans, pricing, and rate limits, giving more control to consumers to customize their experience.

name: Health
about: Factoring in health checks in API consumption, and charging specifically on health checks, or changing plans based upon health results.

name: Encryption
about: Considering the existence of, or strength of encryption as part of the API consumption process.

name: Characters
about: Counting of textual characters as part of the overall API consumption tracking process.

name: Agent
about: Tracking on physical or virtual access to human agents as part of API consumption.

name: Price Per
about: Considering a price per a specific amount of API calls or other metric being applied as part of API consumption.
